/pierce/index.html Franklin Pierce: A Resource Guide] from the Library of Congress\n* [http://www.franklinpierce.ws/ Franklin Pierce Bicentennial]\n* [http://www.c-span.org/video/?125004-1/life-portrait-franklin-pierce \"Life Portrait of Franklin Pierce\"], from [[C-SPAN]]'s ''[[American Presidents: Life Portraits]]'', June 14, 1999\n* [http://www.shapell.org/Collection/Presidents/Pierce-Franklin Franklin Pierce Personal Manuscripts]\n* [https://www.nh.gov/nhdhr/publications/esm/pierce.html Exterior Statues and Memorials \u2013 N.H. Division of Historical Resources]\n*[http://www.bostonmagazine.com/news/2018/01/04/franklin-pierce-train-wreck/ 2018 article on the 14th US President]\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Offices and distinctions\n|list1=\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|us-hs}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Joseph Hammons]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member of the [[List of United States Representatives from New Hampshire|House of Representatives]]<br />from [[New Hampshire's at-large congressional district]]<br />{{small|Seat 3}}|years=1833\u20131837}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Jared W. Williams]]}}\n\n{{s-par|us-sen}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[John Page (New Hampshire)|John Page]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of United States Senators from New Hampshire|United States Senator (Class 3) from New Hampshire]]|years=1837\u20131842|alongside=[[Henry Hubbard]], [[Levi Woodbury]]}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Leonard Wilcox]]}}\n\n{{s-ppo}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Lewis Cass]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] [[List of United States Democratic Party presidential tickets|nominee]] for President of the United States|years=[[1852 United States presidential election|1852]]}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[James Buchanan]]}}\n\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Millard Fillmore]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[President of the United States]]|years=1853\u20131857}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[James Buchanan]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Articles related to Franklin Pierce\n|list1=\n{{US Presidents}}\n{{USDemPresNominees}}\n{{USSenNH}}\n{{Pierce cabi