{"title_page": "Date", "text_new": "{{selfref|For the use of dates on Wikipedia, see [[Wikipedia:Manual of Style/Dates and numbers]].}}\n{{wiktionary|Date|Dates|date|dated|dates}}\n'''Date''' or '''dates'''  may refer to:\n\n*[[Date (fruit)]], the fruit of the date palm (''Phoenix dactylifera'')\n{{TOC right}}\n== Social activity ==\n*[[Dating]], a form of courtship involving social activity, with the aim of assessing a potential partner\n**[[Group date]], wherein a group of individuals go out, with the aim of forming romantic partnerships\n*[[Play date]], an appointment for children to get together for a few hours\n*[[Meeting]] over a meal (e.g.\"lunch date\") or for a planned activity (e.g. \"bowling date\")\n\n==Chronology==\n*[[Calendar date]], a day on a calendar\n** [[Old Style and New Style dates]], used to indicate adoption of the Gregorian calendar in Great Britain and its colonies\n*[[Date (metadata)]], a representation term or class associated  with a data element\n**DATE command, a [[system time]] command for displaying the current date\n*[[Chronological dating]], estimating the age of an object or linguistic artifact\n** [[Dating methodologies in archaeology]], for archaeological artifacts\n**[[Radiometric dating]], a family of techniques used to estimate the period of origin of an object, e.g. \"to carbon-date an artifact\"\n<!-- the above three meanings are more likely targets than the rest, and are hence placed first. -->\n\n== Arts, entertainment, and media ==\n=== Music ===\n*[[Date (band)]], a Swedish dansband\n*[[Date (song)|\"Date\" (song)]], a 2009 song from ''Mr. Houston''\n*[[Date Records]], a subsidiary of Columbia Records\n\n===Film and television ===\n*\"Date\", an [[List of Miranda episodes#ep1.1|episode of the British sitcom ''Miranda'']]\n*[[Dates (TV series)|''Dates'' (TV series)]], a UK Channel 4 series\n*[[Dates (Only Fools and Horses)|\"Dates\" (''Only Fools and Horses'')]], a 1988 episode of the BBC sitcom ''Only Fools and Horses''