ystem time]] command for displaying the current date\n*[[Chronological dating]], estimating the age of an object or linguistic artifact\n** [[Dating methodologies in archaeology]], for archaeological artifacts\n**[[Radiometric dating]], a family of techniques used to estimate the period of origin of an object, e.g. \"to carbon-date an artifact\"\n<!-- the above three meanings are more likely targets than the rest, and are hence placed first. -->\n\n== Arts, entertainment, and media ==\n=== Music ===\n*[[Date (band)]], a Swedish dansband\n*[[Date (song)|\"Date\" (song)]], a 2009 song from ''Mr. Houston''\n*[[Date Records]], a subsidiary of Columbia Records\n\n===Film and television ===\n*\"Date\", an [[List of Miranda episodes#ep1.1|episode of the British sitcom ''Miranda'']]\n*[[Dates (TV series)|''Dates'' (TV series)]], a UK Channel 4 series\n*[[Dates (Only Fools and Horses)|\"Dates\" (''Only Fools and Horses'')]], a 1988 episode of the BBC sitcom ''Only Fools and Horses''\n\n== Organizations and programs ==\n*[[Design Automation and Test in Europe]], a yearly conference on electronic design automation\n*[[Drug, Alcohol, and Tobacco Education]], a substance abuse program in some U.S. schools\n\n== People and kinship groups ==\n*[[Date (surname)]], family name in Japan and elsewhere\n*[[Date clan]], a Japanese feudal clan from the Sengoku period\n\n== Places ==\n*[[Date, Fukushima]], a city located in northern Fukushima, Japan\n*[[Date, Hokkaido]], a city located in Iburi, Hokkaid\u014d, Japan\n*[[Date, South Dakota]], an unincorporated community in the United States\n*[[Date City, California]], an unincorporated community in the United States\n*[[Date District, Fukushima]], a district located in Fukushima, Japan\n*[[Dateland, Arizona]], an unincorporated community in the United States\n\n== See also ==\n*[[Blind date (disambiguation)]]\n*[[Dating (disambiguation)]]\n*[[Double date (disambiguation)]]\n*[[Mystery Date (disambiguation)]]\n\n{{disambiguation|geo}}\n", 